        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Pets can hold aggro yes, but once pet is down (and especially if you have rooted the mob) it will summon you. If you attempt to heal your pet (healing generates aggro you know) and then try to recover your loss of hp for healing (saym vex or ToN) you're asking for a summon.</P><P>Fearkiting or chainstunning, as suggested, might give you some space to breathe but that's it.</P><P></P><P>Lazier, Defiler - Terris Thule<br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21519" target="_blank">My profile</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
