        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Only way to prevent summoning is to keep the agro on your pet. You used to be able to /assist feared npc's, this would let you know who would get summoned when fear broke. You or the pet. This was nerfed apparently so you just have to feel the mob out.<BR> Example is like for an elder wyvern, i would pull with dispell, snare with dooming,fear, and just cast vexing. Everytime fear would wear off my pet would get summoned. If i threw in a splurt lets say, when fear would break i'd get summoned. It's all about controlling agro. For the dain however i don't see it happening heh.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
